| S.No | Question                  | Input                     | Output             | Technique / Pattern              | Variant / Notes                      |
| ---- | ------------------------- | ------------------------- | ------------------ | -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| 1    | Reverse Linked List       | `1->2->3->4->5`           | `5->4->3->2->1`    | Iterative / Recursion            | Can reverse sublist, reverse k-group |
| 2    | Middle of Linked List     | `1->2->3->4->5`           | `3`                | Fast & Slow Pointers             | Return 2nd middle for even length    |
| 3    | Detect Cycle              | `1->2->3->2`              | `true`             | Fast & Slow Pointers             | Return start node variant            |
| 4    | Remove Nth Node From End  | `1->2->3->4->5, n=2`      | `1->2->3->5`       | Two Pointers                     | Single pass solution                 |
| 5    | Merge Two Sorted Lists    | `1->2->4, 1->3->4`        | `1->1->2->3->4->4` | Merge Technique / Recursion      | Iterative variant                    |
| 6    | Add Two Numbers           | `2->4->3 + 5->6->4`       | `7->0->8`          | Simulation / Carry Forward       | Use dummy head                       |
| 7    | Palindrome Linked List    | `1->2->2->1`              | `true`             | Reverse 2nd half + Two Pointers  | Restore list optional                |
| 8    | Intersection of Two Lists | `A:1->2->3->4, B:6->3->4` | `3`                | Two Pointers / Length difference | HashSet variant                      |
| 9    | Delete Node Without Head  | `4->5->1->9, delete 5`    | `4->1->9`          | Copy Next Node                   | Only works if node != tail           |
| 10   | Reorder List              | `1->2->3->4->5`           | `1->5->2->4->3`    | Reverse + Merge                  | Split list into halves first         |


