Reverse Linked List

Input: 1->2->3->4->5

Output: 5->4->3->2->1

Technique/Pattern: Iterative / Recursion

Variants: Reverse a sublist, reverse in groups of k

Middle of Linked List

Input: 1->2->3->4->5

Output: 3

Technique/Pattern: Fast & Slow Pointers

Variants: Return 2nd middle for even length

Detect Cycle

Input: 1->2->3->2 (cycle exists)

Output: true

Technique/Pattern: Fast & Slow Pointers

Variants: Return starting node of cycle

Remove Nth Node From End

Input: 1->2->3->4->5, n=2

Output: 1->2->3->5

Technique/Pattern: Two Pointers

Variants: Single pass solution

Merge Two Sorted Lists

Input: 1->2->4, 1->3->4

Output: 1->1->2->3->4->4

Technique/Pattern: Merge Technique / Recursion

Variants: Iterative merge

Add Two Numbers (Linked List Representation)

Input: 2->4->3 + 5->6->4

Output: 7->0->8

Technique/Pattern: Simulation / Carry Forward

Variants: Use dummy head, handle different lengths

Palindrome Linked List

Input: 1->2->2->1

Output: true

Technique/Pattern: Reverse 2nd half + Two Pointers

Variants: Restore original list after check

Intersection of Two Linked Lists

Input: A:1->2->3->4, B:6->3->4

Output: 3

Technique/Pattern: Two Pointers / Length difference

Variants: HashSet approach

Delete Node Without Head Pointer

Input: 4->5->1->9, delete 5

Output: 4->1->9

Technique/Pattern: Copy Next Node

Variants: Only works if node != tail

Reorder List

Input: 1->2->3->4->5

Output: 1->5->2->4->3

Technique/Pattern: Reverse + Merge

Variants: Split list into halves first
